{
  "texts": [
    "We notice that the rate at which experts are correct when the model is also correct is far from 100%.",
    "This hesitation among experts to rely on the model is also evident from their decision to reveal the model's prediction in just over half of the six provided examples.",
    "P3 (feedback) significantly improves this rate.",
    "13 Despite seemingly being more risk-averse, participants choose \"I don't know\" with a low rate of at most 3%.",
    "The rate at which people are correct when the model is wrong never exceeds 28%."
  ]
}